{"article_id":"WE4kih1WmAQlXIoB","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"\" The 360 \" shows you diverse perspectives on the day ' s top stories and debates .","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Face masks have been at the center of a debate over the U.S. response to the coronavirus pandemic since the early days of the outbreak .","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"In March , public health officials told Americans not to buy masks","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"because their effectiveness","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"in preventing viral transmission","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"was unproven","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"and out of fear","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"that there would be mask shortages for health care workers .","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"A growing body of scientific evidence has led many epidemiologists to believe","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"that the early messaging on masks was faulty .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"The past few months have provided ample evidence","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"that widespread mask wearing could play a significant role","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"in controlling the outbreak .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"In response , an increasing number of state and local governments have made masks mandatory for all indoor activities and outdoor activities","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"when social distancing isn ' t possible .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"These orders have been met with vocal resistance .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"Viral videos of confrontations at stores","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"involving customers","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"who refuse to wear a mask","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"surface regularly .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"Some local law enforcement officials have defied governors","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"by refusing to enforce mask rules .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"Despite the pushback ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"some lawmakers have called for a nationwide mask mandate .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"a federal mask requirement is \" long overdue. \"","depth":13},{"id":26,"text":"The Democratic governors of New Jersey and Illinois have also called for a national mandate .","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"Both President Trump and Vice President Pence have expressed opposition to the idea .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"\" Certainly a national mandate is not in order , \"","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"White House chief of staff Mark Meadows said .","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"Advocates for a national mask mandate say","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"it would make a major difference in the country ' s ability","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"to control the virus","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"and allow for other restrictions to be lifted .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"One study predicted","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"that widespread mask wearing could save up to 33,000 lives by October .","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"A small number of people","depth":14},{"id":37,"text":"who aggressively oppose mask rules","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"shouldn ' t be allowed to dictate policies","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"that could benefit all Americans ,","depth":14},{"id":40,"text":"supporters argue .","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"Having mask rules","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"be decided by state and city governments undercuts what should be a national strategy","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"for fighting the outbreak","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"and creates room","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"for local officials to make unsafe decisions","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"based on political pressure ,","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"some experts say .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"A mask mandate could also have a major economic impact .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Masks would make it possible to safely reopen more businesses and prevent an even more severe economic downturn ,","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"one analysis found .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"The most vocal opponents of mask requirements say","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"the rules are a violation of personal freedom .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"There are also questions","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"about whether a national mask mandate would make much of a difference","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"in preventing viral spread .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"Many of the most affected parts of the country already require masks .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"Forcing a mandate for people in areas with few cases would be unnecessary government overreach ,","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"some argue .","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"Others say","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"a federal mandate would be pointless ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"and that opinions on masks are so entrenched for many people at this point ,","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"even a new nationwide rule is unlikely to change minds","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"and may even cause a backlash .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"Wearing a mask is a small inconvenience with enormous benefits","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"\" Now I understand ,","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"sometimes masks can be a little uncomfortable .","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"But the bottom line is that we know","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"that masks reduce infections","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"and they save lives .","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"... These are basic public health measures","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"that","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"I think","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"should be implemented across the country .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"It ' s not that inconvenient .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"And","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"if it helps us stay open","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"and avoid our hospitals getting overwhelmed ,","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"it feels to me like it ' s well worth the cost. \"","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"- Dr. Ashish Jha to \" Today \"","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"A mask mandate might have prevented the current surge in coronavirus cases","depth":4},{"id":81,"text":"\" I ' ve spoken to several infectious disease experts","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"who say","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"if we had had a national mask mandate","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"as the shelter-in-place restrictions were lifted ,","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"we may not be in the situation","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"that we ' re in now","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"with this continued rise in cases. \"","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"- Allison Aubrey , NPR","depth":5},{"id":90,"text":"The politicization of masks has made the pandemic much worse","depth":4},{"id":91,"text":"than it needed to be","depth":4},{"id":92,"text":"\" Like too much else in our country , this issue has been politicized ,","depth":5},{"id":93,"text":"egged on by a president","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"whose inexplicable refusal","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"to wear a mask","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"sets a terrible example .","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"Unfortunately , his actions gave cover for too many Republican governors to bow to the strident voices","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"opposed to government restrictions on personal liberty ,","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"rather than calling on all of us to act on our personal responsibility","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"to protect others. \"","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"- Karen Hughes , Washington Post","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":203,"left":0,"right":202,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":202,"left":190,"right":201,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":190,"left":180,"right":189,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":180,"left":113,"right":179,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":113,"left":110,"right":112,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":110,"left":1,"right":109,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":109,"left":107,"rig